Several weeks ago, five-year-old Lumka Mketwa drowned in a pit latrine. CAPE TOWN - The Eastern Cape Education Department says it will start installing eight toilets at a Bizana school where a young learner died after falling into a pit toilet. Four portable toilets, which had been donated to Luna Primary, were set alight this week. Several weeks ago, five-year-old Lumka Mketwa drowned in a pit latrine. The department's Mali Mtima: "As the department, we will build eight toilet there. The construction company is supposed to be on site before the end of June. We have given him 21 days because he was awarded the tender."